14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
18 Article – Health – General
19 4–403.
20 (b) Except for a minor patient, unless a patient is notified, a health care provider
21 may not destroy a medical record or laboratory or X–ray report about a patient for 7 years
22 after the record or report is made.
